  "doc_id": "59673",
  "text": "Pairwise synteny blocks were generated between the reference B. bruxellensis assembly and the other haploid assemblies, as well as between the B. naardenensis and B. nanus assemblies. Contigs were placed in chromosome order using Purge Haplotigs [CITATION_1] to generate placement files that were then used to rearrange contigs. Alignments between the assemblies were calculated using NUCmer with sensitive parameters (−b 500 -c 40 -d 0.5 -g 200 -l 12). Genome windows (20 kb windows, 10 kb steps) were generated for the assemblies and a custom script was used to pair syntenic genome windows based on the NUCmer alignments. Concordant overlapping and adjacent windows were merged, and overlapping discordant windows were trimmed. The synteny blocks were then visualized using Circos v0.69.6 [CITATION_2] .",
